        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 1:21PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 120 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northeast of Clarksville, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eagletown, Clarksville, Broken Bow, Idabel, Cerrogordo, Hochatown,
Goodwater, Redland, Haworth, Wright City, Glover, Garvin, West Line,
Oak Hill, Golden, Farmers Hill, Millerton, Negley, Harris, and
Cuthand.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
